<section style="max-width:860px;margin:0 auto;padding:64px 56px;">

  <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1.5px solid rgba(139,26,26,.2)">The Case</div>

  <p style="font-size:19px;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:24px;">The United States government made four specific, documented, legally cognizable promises to formerly enslaved people and their descendants between 1863 and 1866. President Abraham Lincoln approved each one. President Andrew Johnson reversed every single one.</p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:20px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;color:#2a2a28">The consequences are measurable: a $240,000 median household wealth gap, a 29-percentage-point homeownership gap, 90% of Black-owned farmland lost, and HBCUs receiving less than 1% of federal research funding despite producing 40% of Black engineers, 50% of Black teachers, and 70% of Black doctors.</p>

  <p style="margin-bottom:40px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.75;color:#2a2a28">This is not a social phenomenon. It is a federal ledger entry. E5 Enclave is advancing an Executive Order to open that ledger.</p>

  <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1.5px solid rgba(139,26,26,.2)">The Four Broken Promises</div>

  {% set promises = [
