  <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin:52px 0 20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1.5px solid rgba(139,26,26,.2)">What the Order Would Do</div>

  <p style="margin-bottom:20px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.75">The proposed Executive Order would establish:</p>

  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(240px,1fr));gap:16px;margin-bottom:40px;">
    <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e0d5;border-radius:6px;padding:20px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:8px">White House Initiative</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;margin:0;color:#2a2a28">A White House Initiative on Black American Lineage Prosperity, housed at HUD, to coordinate federal programs addressing the wealth gap, homeownership, capital access, food security, and HBCU funding.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e0d5;border-radius:6px;padding:20px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:8px">Presidential Commission</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;margin:0;color:#2a2a28">A President's Commission on Descendants of American Slavery — up to 25 members including Cabinet officials, scholars, HBCU leaders, and community organizations — to advise on implementation and report to the President.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e0d5;border-radius:6px;padding:20px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:8px">Verification Infrastructure</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;margin:0;color:#2a2a28">An Office of ADOS Affairs to administer lineage verification using existing National Archives Freedmen's Bureau records (1.8 million indexed individuals) and Freedman's Bank records — analogous to the Bureau of Indian Affairs enrollment system.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:#fff;border:1px solid #e5e0d5;border-radius:6px;padding:20px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:9px;letter-spacing:.22em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin-bottom:8px">Agency Directives</div>
      <p style="font-size:14px;line-height:1.6;margin:0;color:#2a2a28">Specific directives to USDA (reinstate Black farmer discrimination remediation), HUD (ADOS down payment assistance pilot), Treasury (CDFI infrastructure), SBA (capital access), and ED (HBCU R&D doubling within 3 years).</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="font-family:var(--vc-text);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.32em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--vc-oxblood);margin:52px 0 20px;padding-bottom:10px;border-bottom:1.5px solid rgba(139,26,26,.2)">E5 Enclave's Role</div>

  <p style="margin-bottom:16px;font-size:16px;line-height:1.75">E5 Enclave is not petitioning for this order. We are positioning to implement it. As a registered federal contractor (CAGE 07E88 · UEI H8NGXEYE2HH8) and 501(c)(3) nonprofit, we bring:</p>
  <ul style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.85;color:#2a2a28;padding-left:20px;margin-bottom:32px;">
    <li>The <a href="/black-dragons-initiative/" style="color:var(--vc-oxblood)">Black Distress Index (BDI)</a> — a 50-city data architecture ready to serve as the federal baseline measurement framework the order's reporting requirements would mandate</li>
    <li>The <a href="/programs/lineage-farms/" style="color:var(--vc-oxblood)">Lineage Farms</a> and FarmBlock programs — pilot models for the agricultural and food sovereignty provisions the order would establish at federal scale</li>
    <li>A Coalition of the Willing — the civil society infrastructure an interagency initiative needs to reach communities</li>
    <li>Institutional capacity to contribute to or administer the ADOS lineage verification system</li>
  </ul>

